Dengue/DHF update - Borneo
--------------------------
The risk of dengue fever has been decreasing since 1998 following the
implementation of statewide eradication measures. During the first 6 months
of the year, 185 cases were reported. The highest risk period of
transmission is during, and just after the rainy season. This unpleasant
viral disease is transmitted by mosquitoes that bite mainly in the day.
Reduce bites by covering up and applying insect repellent to exposed areas
of skin. There is no vaccine.
--
Barrett, Peter
<peter.barrett@masta.org>
