Dengue/DHF Update - Costa Rica
------------------------------
Cases of dengue fever have been reported in Puntarenas and Guanacaste on
the Pacific coast, and Limon on the Atlantic coast. This unpleasant virus
is transmitted by day-time biting mosquitoes. As there is no vaccine,
travellers are advised to take steps to avoid mosquito bites.
--
Barrett, Peter
<peter.barrett@masta.org>
