Dengue/DHF Update - Dominican Republic
--------------------------------------
Dengue fever occurs particularly in the rainy season. 3 cases of dengue
fever have been recently reported in travellers returning from the
Dominican Republic and 1 139 cases were reported during the first 9 months
of the year within the country. This unpleasant virus is transmitted by
day-time biting mosquitoes. As there is no vaccine, travellers are advised
to avoid mosquito bites.
--
Barrett, Peter
<peter.barrett@masta.org>
