[4
Date: 13 Oct 2000 22:38:34 -0400
From: Jaime R. Torres <torresj@MailAndNews.com>
Source: Source: El Nacional, 6 Oct 2000 [edited

Dengue Virus Type 3 in Venezuela
---------------------------------
The Venezuelan Ministry of Health and Social Development publicly
acknowledged the occurrence of the first confirmed cases of Dengue virus
type 3 from patients with classic dengue fever in the central and eastern
parts of the country. The serotype identified appears similar to that
currently circulating in Central America. Since 1989, when a large epidemic
of 2 500 cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHR) occurred, Venezuela has
reported large numbers of DHF cases every year, and in 1995 the country
reported the largest regional outbreak with almost 30 000 dengue cases and
5 000 DHF cases.
Although dengue viruses serotypes 1, 2, and 4 have been isolated during
this epidemic, dengue-2 has been by far the predominant serotype. The
official accumulated number of cases of dengue reported during the current
year is 8 000 below that of the same period of 1999 (13 000 vs. 21 000,
respectively). Although the few cases of serotype 3 infection identified so
far correspond to non-hemorrhagic types of the disease, the Venezuelan
population has been extensively exposed to serotypes of dengue virus other
than serotype 3 in the recent past: therefore, the potential for a large
outbreak of dengue hemorrhagic fever exists.
--
Jaime R. Torres; MD
Instituto de Medicina Tropical
Universidad Central de Venezuela
Caracas
<torresj@MailAndNews.com>
